<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Along the lines of PDO::MYSQL_ATTR_INIT_COMMAND, I'd like to see a unified option to specify a query / command or set of commands to execute upon connection of a Zend_Db_Adapter_Abstract instance.</p>

<p>I think this would be reasonably easy to implement as a hook into the abstract _connect() method.</p>

<p>My use case is for setting the NLS_DATE_FORMAT in Oracle connections. At the moment, I'm setting this as soon as the adapter is initialised, thus forcing a connection even if not required, eliminating any lazy loading goodness.</p>

<p>There are of course other applications for such a feature, the above is just an example of where I'd use it.</p>

